<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>CSS Box Model Example</title>

  <style>
    /* 
      ğŸ”¹ The CSS Box Model consists of 4 layers around every HTML element:
      
           â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
           â”‚        Margin (outside)    â”‚
           â”‚  â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”  â”‚
           â”‚  â”‚    Border            â”‚  â”‚
           â”‚  â”‚  â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”  â”‚  â”‚
           â”‚  â”‚  â”‚ Padding        â”‚  â”‚  â”‚
           â”‚  â”‚  â”‚  â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”  â”‚  â”‚  â”‚
           â”‚  â”‚  â”‚  â”‚ Content  â”‚  â”‚  â”‚  â”‚
           â”‚  â”‚  â”‚  â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜  â”‚  â”‚  â”‚
           â”‚  â”‚  â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜  â”‚  â”‚
           â”‚  â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜  â”‚
           â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
      
      Each element is treated as a rectangular box.
    */

    /* Style for the container to visualize spacing */
    body {
      background-color: #f2f2f2;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
    }

    h1 {
      color: darkblue;
    }

    /* 
      ğŸ“¦ Main Box Element 
      - Weâ€™ll apply all box model properties here
    */
    .box {
      width: 250px;                /* Content width only */
      height: 100px;               /* Content height */
      background-color: #add8e6;   /* Light blue background for visibility */
      color: #000;
      margin: 40px auto;           /* Margin: space OUTSIDE the box */
      padding: 20px;               /* Padding: space INSIDE between content and border */
      border: 5px solid #00008b;   /* Border around the padding and content */
      border-radius: 10px;         /* Slightly rounded corners */
      box-shadow: 4px 4px 10px gray; /* Adds shadow to visualize box boundaries */
    }

    /* 
      ğŸ§® Another Box for Comparison 
      - Using different margin, padding, and border values
    */
    .second-box {
      width: 250px;
      height: 100px;
      background-color: #90ee90;   /* Light green */
      color: #000;
      margin: 60px auto;           /* Larger outer spacing */
      padding: 10px;               /* Smaller inner spacing */
      border: 10px dashed darkgreen; /* Thicker border, dashed style */
    }

    /* 
      To show how the total size is calculated:
      
      â¤ Total Element Width = content width + padding-left + padding-right + border-left + border-right + margin-left + margin-right
      â¤ Total Element Height = content height + padding-top + padding-bottom + border-top + border-bottom + margin-top + margin-bottom
    */
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <h1>Understanding the CSS Box Model</h1>

  <div class="box">
    <!-- Content area -->
    This is the <b>content</b> area.<br>
    Padding adds space inside the box,<br>
    and margin adds space outside it.
  </div>

  <div class="second-box">
    This is another box.<br>
    Compare the difference in spacing and borders.
  </div>

  <p><b>Note:</b> The total visible size of an element includes its content, padding, border, and margin.</p>
</body>
</html>
